---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Home
description: Portfolio homepage for Sepideh Mansouri, UI/UX designer in Berlin.
---
<section class="hero-grid">
  <div class="hero-copy">
    <p class="eyebrow">{{ site.home.eyebrow }}</p>
    <h1>{{ site.home.headline }}</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">{{ site.home.intro }}</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="button" href="{{ site.home.ctaPrimary.url }}">{{ site.home.ctaPrimary.label }}</a>
      <a class="button button-secondary" href="{{ site.home.ctaSecondary.url }}">{{ site.home.ctaSecondary.label }}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hero-panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Design lens</p>
    <div class="hero-graphic-frame">
      <img
        class="hero-graphic"
        src="/assets/images/backgrounds/clarity-line.svg"
        alt="An abstract line drawing moving from a dense scribble into a clean path."
        width="1200"
        height="360"
      />
    </div>
    <p class="hero-panel-caption">From complexity to clarity.</p>
    <p class="hero-panel-note">I like taking crowded, uncertain product experiences and shaping them into interfaces that feel calm, legible, and intentional.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stats-grid">
  {% for item in site.home.stats %}
    <article class="stat-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">{{ item.label }}</p>
      <h2>{{ item.value }}</h2>
      <p>{{ item.detail }}</p>
    </article>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section class="section-block">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Featured projects</p>
      <h2>Selected work that combines clarity, structure, and visual tone.</h2>
    </div>
    <a class="text-link" href="/work/">View all work</a>
  </div>
  <div class="project-grid">
    {% for project in collections.featuredProjects %}
      {% include "partials/project-card.njk" %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="split-section">
  <article class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">About my practice</p>
    <h2>My process is rooted in usability, but shaped by content and atmosphere too.</h2>
    <p>I enjoy designing flows that make complex information feel lighter. That means thinking carefully about hierarchy, language, and the small visual decisions that help people trust what they are using.</p>
  </article>
  <aside class="note-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Currently focused on</p>
    <ul class="plain-list">
      <li>Junior UI/UX opportunities</li>
      <li>Portfolio-ready case studies</li>
      <li>Calm, accessible digital products</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="cta-panel">
  <p class="eyebrow">Let’s connect</p>
  <h2>Looking for a thoughtful designer who cares about clarity and human-centered details.</h2>
  <div class="cta-row">
    <a class="button" href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>
    <a class="button button-secondary" href="/resume/">View resume</a>
  </div>
</section>
